When creating a new issue, the cancel button is located on the bottom right hand side to the right of CREATE, which is opposite every standard user interface guideline and habit that OK is on the right hand side and Cancel on the left hand side.  

My team has typed in countless issues and clicked "Cancel" by mistake and had to re-enter the issue.  This is becoming a productivity issue for us and we are considering leaving Jira over it after three years.

We don't think it was always this way (with cancel on the right), but maybe it was and we just hadn't realized until now.

