We use HTML-attachments regularly -- the format is easy to generate, is immediately viewable in a web-browser and most e-mail clients, and can be copy-pasted into one's favourite office application.

Unfortunately, JIRA currently has only basic handling for the files in HTML. It should handle them similar to how it handles images:
* Generate thumbnails for them;
* Open the files in an iframe, when a user clicks on the thumbnail -- as happens with images.

